      "partial_cold_sub_instance": {
        "frequency": "~1 per 20-iter run",
        "signature": "elevated sa_http (~150-280ms) + elevated sa_didauthvp (~50-70ms) — same shape as iter 0 cold but smaller. Lambda routing scatter to less-warm container.",
        "examples": ["run 3 iter 6", "run 7 iters 6,7", "run 8 iter 15", "run 9 iter 18", "run 10 iter 12 (extreme: sa_http=832ms — true mid-run Lambda recycle)", "run 11 iter 17", "run 12 iter 17", "run 13 iter 17"]
      },
      "non_sa_spike": {
        "frequency": "~1 per 30 iterations",
        "signature": "elevated total_ms with warm SA call (sa_http <60ms) — extra time is in Neo4j / sendBoost / logActivity / GC / unknown",
        "examples": ["run 6 iter 5: 1564ms total / 51ms sa_http", "run 12 iter 10: 843ms / 44ms sa_http", "run 13 iters 4,5,15: 772/877/686ms with warm SA"]
      },
      "true_mid_run_lambda_recycle": {
        "frequency": "3 in 270 iterations observed",
        "examples": [
          "run 10 iter 12: sa_http=832ms (1.4% of run)",
          "run 14 iter 10: sa_http=3346ms (post-redeploy, extreme)",
          "run 17 iter 7: sa_http=1017ms (post-second-redeploy)"
        ],
        "signature": "sudden sa_http jump from ~50ms baseline to 800ms-4000ms followed by 2-3 iterations of partial-cold recovery",
        "implication": "Lambda recycles can happen anywhere mid-run, not only at the start. p99 in any single run can be lifted by these. Most likely to occur shortly after a brain redeploy when the SA Lambda also gets fresh traffic patterns."
      },
      "decoupled_didauthvp_stall": {
        "frequency": "~3 per 270 iterations (run 15 iters 15+17, run 17 iter 14)",
        "signature": "warm sa_http (<60ms) but elevated sa_didauthvp (20-67ms vs ~1ms warm). DID-Web cache miss / jose key re-derivation independent of Lambda state.",
        "implication": "Brain-side crypto path has its own brief stalls. Not addressed by Tasks 3-6 directly; would benefit from DID Auth VP caching (deferred design item from earlier sessions)."
      }
    },
    "observations": [
      "Warm-path p50 is rock-solid at ~570ms across 13 independent runs (n=190 iterations).",
      "SA call is consistently fast (~50ms warm). The April-era multi-second cold-start tail for sa_http is gone — staging Lambda is much warmer now.",
      "~510ms of warm total_ms is in non-instrumented phases (Neo4j reads + sendBoost + logActivity + certification). Tasks 4-6 target this directly.",
      "sa_didauthvp on cold paths is highly variable (43-217ms) — that's the brain-side crypto/DID resolution cache initializing.",
      "Run 6 iter 5's 1564ms spike with warm SA call shows that non-SA tail anomalies exist independently of Lambda cold starts — possibly Neo4j slow query, GC pause, or sendBoost cert reissue."
    ]
  },

